body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Robinson Motors. My name is Justin Robinson. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Diane. Could you please provide me with the last four digits of your social security number for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five six seven eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Diane. Additionally, can you confirm your date of birth for security reasons?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: My date of birth is zero one two three, nineteen ninety-four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for verifying your information, Diane. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I have some concerns regarding the recent billing statement I received.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Diane. Let's review the details together. Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Diane. Please feel free to contact us anytime if you need further assistance. Have a wonderful day!
